pohoda-raiffeisenbank (1.8.5) noble; urgency=medium

  * Migrate SharePoint file upload/listing from classic REST
    (\Office365\SharePoint\ClientContext/Folder/File) to Microsoft Graph's
    drive API, for the client-id/secret (app-only) case only - the
    OFFICE365_USERNAME/OFFICE365_PASSWORD user-credential flow is
    unaffected. Switching the token source to Entra ID v2
    (EntraIdAppOnlyAuthenticationContext, 1.8.4) fixed authentication
    against Microsoft Graph, but not against classic SharePoint REST
    (`_api/web/...`): that endpoint checks the token's `appidacr` claim and
    requires `appidacr=2` (certificate-based app-only auth) - a
    client_credentials token obtained with a client *secret* always has
    `appidacr=1` and is unconditionally rejected with "Unsupported app
    only token.", regardless of Sites.Selected permissions granted.
    Confirmed against the daramis tenant: the exact same token/app/site
    that gets HTTP 200 from Microsoft Graph gets HTTP 401 from
    `_api/web/title`. See
    https://techcommunity.microsoft.com/blog/microsoftmissioncriticalblog/avoiding-access-errors-with-sharepoint-app-only-access/4459761
  * Add GraphSharePointClient (plain curl, no vgrem/php-spo dependency):
    uploadFile()/listFiles() against `/v1.0/sites/{id}/drive/root:/...`,
    with one built-in retry (forces a fresh token via
    EntraIdAppOnlyAuthenticationContext::forceRefresh() before retrying).
    Strips the configured OFFICE365_PATH's first segment (the default
    document library's display name, e.g. "Sdilene dokumenty") before
    building Graph paths, since Graph's `drive/root:/` already refers to
    that same library - confirmed live (200 without the segment, 404
    itemNotFound with it).
  * Add GraphApiException, handled by describeRequestException() alongside
    the existing \Office365\Runtime\Http\RequestException so both
    transports report consistently.
  * PohodaBankClientOffice::buildEntraIdContext() (built a classic-REST
    ClientContext) replaced by buildGraphClient() (builds a
    GraphSharePointClient); probeOffice365Auth() now probes the Graph
    scope to match the auth path actually in use.
  * Wired into pohodaSQL-raiffeisenbank-statements-sharepoint.php,
    raiffeisenbank-statements-sharepoint-uploader.php,
    raiffeisenbank-statements-sharepoint-checker.php and
    pohoda-sharepoint-link-fixer.php via local $doUpload/$doList closures,
    so the rest of each script doesn't need to know which transport
    backs the client-credential case.
  * NOTE: the uploaded file's reported URL changes format for the
    client-credential case, from the classic
    ".../_layouts/15/download.aspx?SourceUrl=..." link to Microsoft
    Graph's own driveItem `webUrl` - both are valid direct links to the
    file. The user-credential flow's link format is unchanged.

 -- vitex <info@vitexsoftware.cz>  Tue, 07 Jul 2026 08:00:00 +0200

pohoda-raiffeisenbank (1.8.4) noble; urgency=medium

  * Add EntraIdAppOnlyAuthenticationContext: real Entra ID (Azure AD) v2
    app-only client_credentials authentication for SharePoint, replacing
    the Azure ACS app-only flow Microsoft fully retired on 2026-04-02 (no
    extension possible for any tenant, see
    https://learn.microsoft.com/sharepoint/dev/sp-add-ins/retirement-announcement-for-azure-acs).
    Confirmed against the daramis tenant: ACS's token endpoint still issues
    a syntactically valid token, but SharePoint Online now rejects it on
    the actual REST call (HTTP 401 {"error":"invalid_request"}) regardless
    of credentials or the tenant's DisableCustomAppAuthentication setting.
    Implements Office365\Runtime\Auth\IAuthenticationContext directly
    (rather than extending the SDK's AuthenticationContext, whose
    authenticateRequest() only builds the Authorization header for its own
    ACSTokenProvider/AADTokenProvider instances) so it can be passed
    straight to `new ClientContext($url, $authCtx)`.
  * Add PohodaBankClientOffice::buildEntraIdContext() to construct a
    ClientContext authenticated this way from OFFICE365_TENANT/_SITE/
    _CLIENTID/_CLSECRET, used by pohodaSQL-raiffeisenbank-statements-sharepoint.php,
    raiffeisenbank-statements-sharepoint-uploader.php,
    raiffeisenbank-statements-sharepoint-checker.php and
    pohoda-sharepoint-link-fixer.php for the client-id/secret auth case (the
    OFFICE365_USERNAME/_PASSWORD user-credential flow is unchanged, ACS
    retirement doesn't affect it)
  * Rework probeOffice365Auth() to independently test the Entra ID v2 flow
    instead of the now-permanently-dead ACS one, and generalize
    withSharePointRetry()'s second parameter from SDK credentials
    (ACS-specific reset via withCredentials()) to a plain reset callback, so
    it works for EntraIdAppOnlyAuthenticationContext::forceRefresh() too
  * NOTE: the app registration behind OFFICE365_CLIENTID/OFFICE365_CLSECRET
    still needs the Microsoft Graph "Sites.Selected" application permission,
    admin-consented, and an explicit grant on the target site via
    `POST /sites/{siteId}/permissions` - confirmed by hand against daramis
    that a valid Entra ID v2 token alone is not sufficient without it
    (SharePoint responds "Unsupported app only token.")

pohoda-raiffeisenbank (1.8.3) noble; urgency=medium

  * Add PohodaBankClientOffice::withSharePointRetry(): retries a SharePoint
    operation once after resetting the ClientContext's credentials.
    \Office365\Runtime\Auth\ACSTokenProvider hands ACS's decoded response
    straight to AuthenticationContext as the access token without checking
    the HTTP status, so a transient ACS hiccup leaves a broken token
    (e.g. {"error":"invalid_request"}) cached on the context; since
    AuthenticationContext only re-acquires a token when none is cached yet,
    every further request - not just the one that hit the hiccup - then
    fails identically, and a plain executeQuery() retry would resend the
    same broken token. Calling ClientContext::withCredentials() again
    installs a fresh, unauthenticated AuthenticationContext, forcing a real
    new ACS token request on the next attempt.
  * Wire it into the SharePoint file listing and PDF/XML upload calls in
    pohodaSQL-raiffeisenbank-statements-sharepoint.php and
    raiffeisenbank-statements-sharepoint-uploader.php

pohoda-raiffeisenbank (1.8.2) noble; urgency=medium

  * Add PohodaBankClientOffice::probeOffice365Auth(): independently
    re-acquires an ACS app-only token for the same OFFICE365_* credential
    outside the SDK, so a failed SharePoint upload/list can be diagnosed as
    "auth itself is broken" vs "auth is fine, the REST call failed for
    another reason" without needing production access. Memoized per run;
    wired into describeRequestException() so every existing call site gets
    it for free.
  * Extract describeRequestException()/probeOffice365Auth() out of
    PohodaBankClient into a new PohodaBankClientOffice subclass, keeping the
    Office365/SharePoint-only diagnostics separate from the generic Pohoda
    bank client used by RaiffeisenBank statement/transaction import; update
    pohodaSQL-raiffeisenbank-statements-sharepoint.php,
    raiffeisenbank-statements-sharepoint-uploader.php and
    pohoda-sharepoint-link-fixer.php to call the new class

